> Any ideas/info/contact on cable replacment for a good thermostat? Or
> do I just use an old shoe lace and duct tape.

Go to the hardware and buy some 1/32" stainless steel aircraft cable and a
ferrule to crimp onto the end. It will cost $1 or less to make this.

